/******************************************** JAVA ***************************************/

Optimal Solution â€“  Using a stack and a result array, we store the indices of future days with higher temperatures, and for 
                    each day calculate and store the number of days to wait until a warmer temperature is found, then return 
                    the result array.

class Solution {
    public int[] dailyTemperatures(int[] temperatures) {
        // Stack to store indices of days
        // It maintains a monotonic decreasing stack based on temperatures
        Stack<Integer> st = new Stack<>();
        int n = temperatures.length;
        // Result array to store the number of days to wait for a warmer temperature
        int[] res = new int[n];
        // Traverse the array from right to left
        for (int idx = n - 1; idx >= 0; idx--) {
            // Remove all indices from the stack whose temperatures
            // are less than or equal to the current day's temperature
            while (!st.isEmpty() && temperatures[idx] >= temperatures[st.peek()]) {
                st.pop();
            }
            // If stack is not empty, the top element is the next warmer day
            if (!st.isEmpty()) {
                // Difference of indices gives the number of days to wait
                res[idx] = st.peek() - idx;
            }
            // Push current index onto the stack
            st.push(idx);
        }
        // Return the result array
        return res;
    }
}
Time Complexity :- O(N).
Space Complexity :- O(N)
